OL,3,CTributes to 'extraordinary'
OL,4,CHillsborough campaigner who lost 18-
OL,5,Cyear-old son
OL,7,F"The lawyers feared him, he knew more
OL,8,Fthan them, he served as a magistrate
OL,9,Fso he knew the law and he believed in
OL,10,Fit - sadly the law let him down."
OL,12,FHe added: "When it came to
OL,13,FHillsborough, Barry was the ultimate
OL,14,Fexample, the pinnacle, of what the
OL,15,Fgovernment and everyone else
OL,16,Funderestimated about the families.
OL,18,F"He did this all out of love, the love
OL,19,Ffor his son Christopher, and he never
OL,20,Fgave up.
OL,26,@zD@AOU
