OL,3,CTributes to 'extraordinary'
OL,4,CHillsborough campaigner who lost 18-
OL,5,Cyear-old son
OL,7,F"Barry Devonside lost his son
OL,8,FChristopher in the Hillsborough
OL,9,FDisaster and from that day on he never
OL,10,Fstopped fighting for justice.
OL,12,F"Not only for the victims who lost
OL,13,Ftheir lives but also for the survivors
OL,14,Fand the innocent fans who were
OL,15,Fdisgracefully lied about and blamed.
OL,17,F"I had the honour of meeting Barry for
OL,18,Fthe first time in 2013 and it has been
OL,19,Fa privilege to have known him."
